g the same `managedPrefix` guard already used for Claude (line 500) so we never touch user-authored hooks.\n     c. Reuses the same `hooks.yaml` manifest schema (`events`, `matcher`, `script`, `timeout`, `agents`). Codex's matcher rules: `PreToolUse`/`PostToolUse` match on tool name, `SessionStart` on `startup|resume`, `UserPromptSubmit`/`Stop` ignore matcher.\n\n3. **Version-gate the sync.** Codex versions before v0.116.0 do not implement `UserPromptSubmit`; older still don't have hooks at all. `syncResourcesToVersion` (`src/lib/versions.ts`) knows the version it is syncing into. Before applying hooks for Codex:\n   - Parse the version from the version dir name.\n   - Define a floor (e.g. `CODEX_HOOKS_MIN_VERSION = '0.116.0'`) in `src/lib/agents.ts` next to the Codex config.\n   - If installed version < floor, skip hook registration with a single visible warning (`hooks skipped: codex@<version> < 0.116.0`). Do NOT fail the sync.\n   - If a hook in `hooks.yaml` lists an event the installed version doesn't support yet (e.g. `UserPromptSubmit` on a future floor), skip just that event with a warning, register the rest.\n\n4. **Surface in `agents view` and `agents hooks list`.** When Codex is below the floor, mark hooks as `unsupported (codex@<v> < 0.116.0)` instead of `synced`. Reuses the existing scope/status rendering.\n\n5. **Tests.**\n   - `src/lib/__tests__/hooks.test.ts` (new, 1:1 with `hooks.ts`): cover the Codex TOML+JSON writer, the version-gate skip path, and the matcher-less events.\n   - Use real temp dirs + real file writes; no mocks (per repo testing rules).\n\n## Acceptance\n\nEnd-to-end on a real machine, with both `~/.agents/versions/codex/0.113.0` and `~/.agents/versions/codex/0.116.0` installed (already present locally per `ls ~/.agents/versions/codex/`):\n\n- `agents hooks add <repo> --agents codex` succeeds.\n- After `agents use codex@0.116.0` → `agents pull` (or `agents sync`):\n  - `~/.codex/config.toml` contains `[features] codex_hooks = true`.\